### task-10.outline
Task: 10
Title: Anthropic inbound route, translator, SSE encoder, server mount, and tests
Phase: 4
Route: full
Slice: Slice 5 (Anthropic Inbound)
Dependencies: 09 (AnthropicChatAdapter, factory)
Scope: Create the full Anthropic inbound HTTP stack: request translator (Anthropic-format body → FusionRequest), SSE encoder (FusionStreamEvent → all 6 Anthropic SSE event types in documented sequence with both event: and data: fields), and Hono route handling POST /v1/messages. Mount the new route in server.ts. Create unit test for translator and integration test for the route. All Anthropic-specific types and SSE event shapes are confined to this directory. Reuses the same FusionService unchanged.
Acceptance Criteria: AC-11 (full — /v1/messages route + 6-event SSE)
NFRs: NFR-1, NFR-2 (Hono confined to infrastructure/inbound/http), NFR-3 (no Anthropic types leak to domain/app)
Gate Criteria: Phase 4 Gate 1 (6-event SSE sequence with event: and data: fields), Phase 4 Gate 2 (no type leakage)
Files:
  - src/infrastructure/inbound/http/anthropic/translator.ts (CREATE) — Export anthropicRequestToFusion(body: Record<string, unknown>): FusionRequest. Maps Anthropic request fields (system, messages with content blocks, max_tokens, model) to canonical FusionRequest. Export fusionStreamToAnthropicSSE(events: AsyncIterable<FusionStreamEvent>, model: string): AsyncIterable<string>. Emits all 6 event types in documented sequence: message_start → content_block_start → content_block_delta → content_block_stop → message_delta → message_stop. Each event has both event: and data: SSE fields. Delegates to encodeAnthropicSSE for low-level formatting.
  - src/infrastructure/inbound/http/anthropic/sse-encoder.ts (CREATE) — Low-level SSE formatter: encodeAnthropicSSE(events: AsyncIterable<FusionStreamEvent>, model: string): AsyncIterable<string>. For progress events: emits ": heartbeat" keep-alive comments. For content: emits event: message_start / content_block_start / content_block_delta / content_block_stop / message_delta / message_stop with corresponding data: JSON. message_start includes model and usage stub. message_delta includes stop_reason and cumulative usage. message_stop is the terminal event.
  - src/infrastructure/inbound/http/anthropic/route.ts (CREATE) — Export createAnthropicRoute(fusionService: FusionService): (c: Context) => Promise<Response>. Parses Anthropic-format body, calls anthropicRequestToFusion(), runs fusionService.runFusion(), encodes via fusionStreamToAnthropicSSE(), returns SSE response using Hono streamSSE().
  - src/infrastructure/inbound/http/server.ts (MODIFY) — Import createAnthropicRoute from './anthropic/route.js'. Inside createServer(): add app.post('/v1/messages', createAnthropicRoute(fusionService)).
  - src/infrastructure/inbound/http/anthropic/translator.test.ts (CREATE) — node:test suite: Anthropic → Fusion request translation (system, messages, max_tokens, model), stream event → Anthropic SSE mapping for all 6 event types, keep-alive comment emission, error event handling.
  - src/infrastructure/inbound/http/anthropic/route.integration.test.ts (CREATE) — node:test integration suite: Hono app with POST /v1/messages using streamSSE, verifies SSE response with all 6 event types in sequence, keep-alive comments, and error handling.
